WEBVTT

00:02.261 --> 00:04.390
I swear this is the last one.

00:04.415 --> 00:05.758
You positive? 'Cause I'm just not sure

00:05.782 --> 00:07.660
you kept enough of our old stuff.

00:08.048 --> 00:10.127
Well, I mean, look at those booties.

00:10.152 --> 00:13.198
Come on. How could
I get rid of those booties?

00:13.223 --> 00:15.648
Because... Ew,
they're covered in mildew.

00:15.673 --> 00:17.551
Wow. Zoey. I didn't realize

00:17.576 --> 00:19.664
you were such a fan
of Cabbage Patch Kids.

00:19.689 --> 00:21.333
Actually, that was mine.

00:21.358 --> 00:22.421
Oh.

00:22.446 --> 00:23.703
And this...

00:23.728 --> 00:24.953
Mine as well.

00:24.978 --> 00:26.750
Oh, babe.

00:26.775 --> 00:29.382
No wonder you became such a
bleeding-heart public defender.

00:29.690 --> 00:31.203
You really care, bear.

00:31.228 --> 00:35.140
Yeah, David was always a very
sweet, sensitive child.

00:35.165 --> 00:36.515
How do you describe me?

00:36.540 --> 00:39.265
- You were more inquisitive.
- Mm.

00:39.290 --> 00:42.710
You only wanted science
and engineering toys.

00:42.735 --> 00:44.980
Damn straight. These
were my gateway drugs

00:45.005 --> 00:48.257
to straight As and a
stunning scholastic career.

00:49.868 --> 00:51.281
Um, if it's okay with Zoey,

00:51.306 --> 00:53.390
you can take whatever
you want for the baby.

00:53.415 --> 00:57.459
Oh, yeah. Um, I'm good. All yours.

00:57.484 --> 01:00.085
Be right back.
I'm just gonna make a quick call.

01:01.257 --> 01:02.507
You forgot another one.

01:02.532 --> 01:05.796
So, I'll meet you at the
flower market in an hour?

01:06.852 --> 01:09.390
I'm excited, too, Jessica.

01:09.415 --> 01:11.289
Okay. Bye.

01:12.372 --> 01:13.875
Jessica?

01:14.676 --> 01:16.398
Why so secretive?

01:17.750 --> 01:20.210
I just... I feel weird

01:20.235 --> 01:23.750
talking about work stuff
in front of your dad.

01:24.243 --> 01:25.687
Hm.

01:25.977 --> 01:28.015
Since we're alone for a minute,

01:28.040 --> 01:29.921
what new on the Simon front?

01:29.946 --> 01:31.359
You'd be very proud.

01:31.384 --> 01:33.554
I haven't texted him
back in a couple days.

01:33.579 --> 01:35.328
How do you feel about that?

01:35.353 --> 01:38.932
Um, only minor withdrawals.

01:38.957 --> 01:40.226
Hm.

01:41.726 --> 01:44.234
Oh, my gosh. Dad, you remember this?

01:44.259 --> 01:46.234
Wow, it actually still works.

01:58.970 --> 02:00.445
Oh, you lost.

02:00.470 --> 02:03.758
All right, okay,
I hate to spoil this lovely symphony,

02:03.783 --> 02:06.695
but can we focus?
I've got to get to work soon.

02:06.720 --> 02:08.663
We're good to build
the crib tonight, right?

02:08.689 --> 02:10.767
Um, you know,
I'm still prepping for trial.

02:10.792 --> 02:13.468
The... the O'Reilly case?

02:13.692 --> 02:16.210
Think it's going to be another
late night at the office.

02:16.235 --> 02:17.523
Again?

02:17.967 --> 02:19.718
This case has taken over your life.

02:19.743 --> 02:21.273
I'm not happy about it either.

02:21.298 --> 02:23.023
Yeah, it's just, we said we were gonna

02:23.048 --> 02:24.468
get cracking on this weeks ago,

02:24.493 --> 02:28.040
and it seems like it's never
the right time with you.

02:28.444 --> 02:29.445
Now that we know it's a boy,

02:29.469 --> 02:30.782
we can really start to get organized.

02:30.806 --> 02:33.015
Em, I get it, okay? I get it.

02:33.137 --> 02:34.835
All right? I'm doing
the best that I can.

02:34.860 --> 02:37.609
Everything... okay?

02:37.634 --> 02:39.523
- Uh-huh.
- Uh-huh.

02:42.755 --> 02:46.414
♪ You've been talking in your sleep ♪

02:46.742 --> 02:48.265
♪ Oh, oh ♪

02:48.290 --> 02:52.281
♪ Things you never say to me ♪

02:52.306 --> 02:53.684
♪ Oh, oh ♪

02:53.709 --> 02:57.437
♪ Tell me that you've had enough ♪

02:57.545 --> 03:00.382
♪ Of our love ♪

03:00.407 --> 03:03.578
♪ Our love ♪

03:04.189 --> 03:09.101
♪ Just give me a reason,
just a little bit's enough ♪

03:09.126 --> 03:12.882
♪ Just a second,
we're not broken, just bent ♪

03:12.907 --> 03:17.171
♪ And we can learn to love again ♪

03:17.465 --> 03:20.257
♪ I'm sorry I don't understand ♪

03:20.282 --> 03:23.061
♪ Where all of this is coming from ♪

03:23.086 --> 03:26.565
♪ I thought that we were fine ♪

03:26.590 --> 03:28.750
♪ Oh, we had everything ♪

03:28.775 --> 03:32.476
♪ You've been having real bad dreams ♪

03:32.501 --> 03:33.796
- ♪ Oh, oh ♪
- ♪ Oh, oh ♪

03:33.821 --> 03:37.515
♪ There's nothing more
than empty sheets ♪

03:37.540 --> 03:40.886
- ♪ Between our love ♪
- ♪ Between our love ♪

03:40.911 --> 03:44.796
- ♪ Our love ♪
- ♪ Our love ♪

03:44.821 --> 03:46.906
♪ Just give me a reason ♪

03:46.931 --> 03:49.476
♪ Just a little bit's enough ♪

03:49.501 --> 03:53.314
♪ Just a second,
we're not broken, just bent ♪

03:53.339 --> 03:55.985
♪ And we can learn to love again ♪

03:56.010 --> 03:57.721
♪ I've never stopped ♪

03:57.746 --> 04:01.656
♪ You're still written in
the scars on my heart ♪

04:01.681 --> 04:04.093
♪ We're not broken, just bent ♪

04:04.118 --> 04:08.921
♪ And we can learn to love again ♪

04:18.151 --> 04:19.773
You...

04:19.798 --> 04:21.875
sure everything's okay?

04:21.899 --> 04:23.515
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

04:26.657 --> 04:28.351
Bull...

04:29.492 --> 04:32.892
Synced & corrected by QueenMaddie
www.addic7ed.com

04:33.771 --> 04:35.054
Guess what?

04:35.079 --> 04:38.334
I just heard my first actual duet.

04:38.359 --> 04:41.437
Two people singing the same song,
at the same time.

04:41.462 --> 04:43.106
I am very aware of what a duet is.

04:43.130 --> 04:46.076
But now it raises all sorts
of questions for us to tackle.

04:46.100 --> 04:48.164
Ugh, why do I even
answer the phone this early?

04:48.189 --> 04:50.053
I am an artist, Zoey, and my brain

04:50.078 --> 04:52.816
does not like functioning
until night o'clock.

04:52.840 --> 04:54.945
But I just don't know which one to help.

04:54.970 --> 04:56.086
Or maybe it's both.

04:56.110 --> 04:59.593
And I'm sure we can figure all
this out over drinks tonight.

04:59.618 --> 05:01.196
Okay, fine. Where do you wanna go?

05:01.221 --> 05:02.792
Somewhere basic and hetero.

05:02.817 --> 05:04.953
I'm in the mood for potato skins.

05:04.978 --> 05:06.406
<i>'Kay, bye.</i>

05:07.855 --> 05:09.733
Now that the SprqPoint
watch is out there

05:09.757 --> 05:13.003
dazzling users with its sheer
brilliance of engineering,

05:13.027 --> 05:15.305
we are ready to move
on to a new project.

05:15.329 --> 05:17.203
However, before we do,

05:17.228 --> 05:19.508
your manager, Zoey, feels that we need

05:19.533 --> 05:22.592
to foster a more open,
honest work environment,

05:22.617 --> 05:25.881
and that's why, today,
we'll be sharing the results

05:25.906 --> 05:28.699
of the anonymous peer reviews
that you wrote about each other

05:28.724 --> 05:30.156
a few weeks back.

05:30.625 --> 05:31.821
Hmm?

05:31.846 --> 05:35.312
I thought the peer reviews
were for internal use only.

05:35.487 --> 05:37.427
What's the good of bad
news if you can't share it?

05:37.451 --> 05:39.540
Am I right? Zoey and I will
meet with you individually

05:39.564 --> 05:41.781
to go over the results
of what your friends

05:41.806 --> 05:44.085
and colleagues had to say about you.

05:44.110 --> 05:46.101
Tobin Batra.

05:46.126 --> 05:47.539
- Hit me.
- Okay, well,

05:47.564 --> 05:50.539
aside from several of them commenting

05:50.564 --> 05:53.514
on your extreme overuse
of the eggplant emoji,

05:53.539 --> 05:55.378
in general, their feedback
regarding your work

05:55.402 --> 05:57.736
was that it is... adequate.

05:58.971 --> 06:00.315
Boo-yah!

06:00.340 --> 06:02.632
Love barely meeting expectations.

06:05.753 --> 06:08.253
Max...

06:09.523 --> 06:10.981
Oh, Richman.

06:11.006 --> 06:13.351
Yep. Same last name
I had five years ago...

06:13.376 --> 06:14.820
when I started working here.

06:14.845 --> 06:16.966
Uh, "Lacks drive," "Is complacent,"

06:16.991 --> 06:19.669
"Doesn't show initiative,"
"Takes the easy way out,"

06:19.693 --> 06:23.507
"Settles when he could
be working much harder."

06:23.531 --> 06:25.141
- All...
- Bad.

06:25.165 --> 06:26.165
Constructive.

06:26.190 --> 06:28.669
Lot of great stuff to build on.

06:28.694 --> 06:30.578
Is it... great?

06:30.722 --> 06:32.733
Feels not so great.

06:33.742 --> 06:36.519
Okay, Leif, ready to hear what
your colleagues had to say?

06:36.544 --> 06:38.388
Only if you feel it's necessary.

06:38.412 --> 06:40.991
I know that all three of us know

06:41.015 --> 06:44.062
that, uh, as the best programmer here,

06:44.220 --> 06:45.929
I'm, uh... what's the word? Beloved.

06:45.954 --> 06:48.197
Um, okay.

06:48.222 --> 06:51.668
"Leif is self-righteous
and overly ambitious."

06:51.692 --> 06:53.336
"His 'aw-shucks' demeanor

06:53.360 --> 06:56.673
"masks a relentless drive
to win at all costs,

06:56.697 --> 06:59.031
"which is more
alienating than endearing.

06:59.056 --> 07:01.351
That's probably why he
didn't get the promotion."

07:03.486 --> 07:04.897
Wow.

07:04.922 --> 07:07.664
Uh, I was... I was not expecting that.

07:08.375 --> 07:10.086
May I ask who...

07:10.110 --> 07:12.489
It's anonymous, the peer reviews.

07:12.513 --> 07:14.679
It's called "anonymous peer review."

07:15.473 --> 07:18.351
Well, uh, thank you

07:18.376 --> 07:22.359
for your... honesty

07:22.875 --> 07:25.984
and your feedback.

07:31.414 --> 07:33.776
Well... that was fun.

07:33.801 --> 07:35.512
Wait, you never said what
people wrote about me.

07:35.536 --> 07:37.080
I'm sure the team had thoughts.

07:37.104 --> 07:38.848
Oh, "the team had thoughts."

07:38.872 --> 07:40.450
But you know, "misogyny, misogyny."

07:40.474 --> 07:43.093
I think you're crushing it.
That's all that matters.

07:47.140 --> 07:48.959
Is this the kind of
place you had in mind?

07:48.983 --> 07:51.227
Men in Dockers, full-calorie beer,

07:51.251 --> 07:53.570
corporate types looking
to unwind, it's perfect.

07:53.595 --> 07:55.331
I invited Max to join us, too.

07:55.356 --> 07:56.860
He had a rough day at work.
I hope that's okay.

07:56.884 --> 07:58.118
Fine with me. But before he gets here,

07:58.142 --> 08:01.195
let's talk about this duet.
Was it romantic? Depressing?

08:01.220 --> 08:04.007
It was... tortured.

08:04.032 --> 08:05.687
Oh! The best duets are.

08:05.712 --> 08:09.560
My brother and sister-in-law
were singing at each other.

08:09.585 --> 08:11.514
She seemed more upset than he did.

08:11.538 --> 08:13.710
Seems like she's the one
you're supposed to help, then.

08:13.735 --> 08:16.247
Oh! I hope not.

08:16.272 --> 08:18.054
Emily and I aren't really the tightest.

08:18.079 --> 08:22.226
She's kind of acerbic,
I'm kind of stand-offish.

08:22.251 --> 08:23.821
You two would be great
in a female cop show.

08:23.845 --> 08:25.656
My brother's totally harmless.

08:25.681 --> 08:27.258
I'm sure she's upset about something

08:27.283 --> 08:28.461
that isn't even his fault.

08:28.486 --> 08:29.996
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

08:30.021 --> 08:31.533
Autumn's coming, too,
but she thought she saw

08:31.557 --> 08:33.289
a rainbow in an oil slick outside,

08:33.313 --> 08:35.859
so she's still absorbing its beauty.

08:35.884 --> 08:37.671
You know, you've been very tight-lipped

08:37.696 --> 08:38.890
about Autumn since Napa.

08:38.914 --> 08:40.445
Did you have a good time?

08:40.470 --> 08:42.410
Uh, yeah. Napa was fun.

08:42.436 --> 08:45.448
I'm just not sure we're
totally on the same wavelength,

08:45.472 --> 08:48.318
a word she uses endlessly, by the way.

08:48.342 --> 08:52.101
I thought you dug her whole
adorable flower child...

08:52.126 --> 08:53.804
Meets-young-Kristin-Chenoweth vibe.

08:53.829 --> 08:55.206
Autumn hated being on a schedule

08:55.231 --> 08:57.375
and wanted to just
run through the fields.

08:57.400 --> 09:01.031
She unironically chased a
butterfly for 37 minutes.

09:01.056 --> 09:02.351
- Oh, my God, Max.
- Hi.

09:02.376 --> 09:05.088
You better not be telling
them about Napa without me.

09:05.113 --> 09:08.039
It was pure magic.

09:12.489 --> 09:14.133
Kick it!

09:15.293 --> 09:16.793
Will you excuse me?

09:27.606 --> 09:31.531
♪ You wake up late for school,
man, you don't wanna go ♪

09:34.765 --> 09:37.773
♪ You ask your mom, please,
but she still says ♪

09:37.798 --> 09:39.218
♪ No ♪

09:41.951 --> 09:45.796
♪ You missed two classes
and no homework ♪

09:48.960 --> 09:52.140
♪ But your teacher preaches
class like you're some kind of ♪

09:52.165 --> 09:53.710
♪ Jerk ♪

09:55.397 --> 09:57.109
♪ You gotta fight ♪

09:57.596 --> 09:59.320
♪ For your right ♪

09:59.718 --> 10:02.835
♪ To party ♪

10:08.337 --> 10:10.179
Still working.
I'll be home a little later.

10:10.204 --> 10:11.204
Love you.

