Just a minute!

37:51.522 --> 37:53.439
- Hi.
- Sorry, I know it's late.

37:53.464 --> 37:56.291
I just needed to talk through
something with somebody.

37:56.316 --> 37:57.744
With you.

37:57.769 --> 38:00.025
Of course. Uh, come in.

38:00.720 --> 38:02.220
- Um...
- What's wrong?

38:02.245 --> 38:04.409
I was going through some old
emails between me and my dad,

38:04.433 --> 38:05.994
just normal everyday stuff.

38:06.019 --> 38:07.759
A diner opened up down the street.

38:07.784 --> 38:09.549
The fantasy football draft.

38:09.964 --> 38:13.525
But there was this moment
where his whole tenor changed.

38:16.199 --> 38:20.424
It's like a bleakness,
or something took over,

38:20.728 --> 38:22.772
that I completely missed at the time.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.509
I'll show you.

38:24.935 --> 38:28.142
It's, uh, right here.
Pulled it up a second ago.

38:28.167 --> 38:29.713
I just...

38:31.402 --> 38:34.369
Could I have stopped him
from going through with it?

38:36.134 --> 38:37.711
Did I...

38:41.478 --> 38:45.533
Did I fail him when he
needed me the most?

38:50.510 --> 38:52.174
Simon,

38:52.847 --> 38:54.588
it's...

38:58.285 --> 39:01.189
... entirely possible

39:01.214 --> 39:03.845
that you failed to see the signs
that your dad was in trouble.

39:03.870 --> 39:07.049
I know. That's what I think, too.

39:12.112 --> 39:13.812
But maybe...

39:17.261 --> 39:19.033
... there's nothing more
you could have done

39:19.058 --> 39:21.744
because your dad didn't want
or wasn't open to your help.

39:26.532 --> 39:28.463
It's hard to admit...

39:29.691 --> 39:32.611
that we fail sometimes, but, um...

39:33.656 --> 39:35.181
it's true.

39:35.523 --> 39:37.267
And...

39:38.705 --> 39:42.541
you know, we don't know
what was going on in his head.

39:44.611 --> 39:46.924
And, you, living with all this,

39:46.949 --> 39:50.525
carrying some...

39:51.124 --> 39:53.252
vague guilt...

39:53.522 --> 39:57.150
doesn't help you move forward.

40:03.674 --> 40:05.486
Thank you.

40:06.328 --> 40:09.666
For the worst pep talk ever?

40:11.136 --> 40:12.436
It was bad.

40:12.461 --> 40:15.941
Yeah, it was actually...

40:16.115 --> 40:17.845
pretty great.

40:18.673 --> 40:21.516
But thank you for not trying to fix me,

40:22.283 --> 40:23.666
or make me feel better.

40:23.691 --> 40:26.025
Thanks for just being...

40:27.351 --> 40:29.095
real.

40:29.687 --> 40:31.291
Any time.

